Questions:
What should you do if you decide to withdraw your consent to participate in the DE FACTO 2 study?
A) Continue to participate in the study activities until the scheduled end;
B) Inform Mme Aude-Marie Foucaut and Mme Albane Aumaitre of your decision to withdraw;
C) Return the connected watch immediately to the study coordinators;
D) Pay a penalty for early withdrawal from the study.

Correct answer: B

Which of the following is a potential discomfort mentioned in the DE FACTO 2 study consent form?
A) The need to attend sessions either in person or virtually and to be available for evaluations up to one year post-intervention;
B) The risk of severe allergic reactions to the materials used in the study;
C) The possibility of experiencing significant weight loss as a direct result of the study activities;
D) The chance of personal data being shared publicly without the participant's consent.

Correct answer: A) The need to attend sessions either in person or virtually and to be available for evaluations up to one year post-intervention.

How will your personal data be handled in the DE FACTO 2 study to ensure confidentiality?
A) Personal data will be published with your name and contact details for transparency;
B) Data from the connected watch will be linked to your name and made publicly available;
C) Personal data will be anonymized with a code system to prevent identification and protected by professional secrecy;
D) All personal data will be shared with third-party commercial entities for research purposes.

Correct answer: C) Personal data will be anonymized with a code system to prevent identification and protected by professional secrecy.
